members.name: MSGestureEvent.expansion
members.description: The diameter of the gesture area. For example, the distance between fingers.

members.name: MSGestureEvent.gestureObject
members.description: Returns the MSGesture object for this gesture event.

members.name: MSGestureEvent.rotation
members.description: Amount of rotation (in radians) since the previous MSGestureEvent of the current gesture. Positive values indicate clockwise rotation; negative values indicate anticlockwise rotation.

members.name: MSGestureEvent.scale
members.description: The difference in scale (for zoom gestures) from the previous MSGestureEvent of the current gesture.

members.name: MSGestureEvent.translationX
members.description: Distance traversed along the X-axis since the previous MSGestureEvent of the current gesture

members.name: MSGestureEvent.translationY
members.description: Distance traversed along the Y-axis since the previous MSGestureEvent of the current gesture

members.name: MSGestureEvent.velocityExpansion
members.description: The velocity of the expansion of the gesture area.

members.name: MSGestureEvent.velocityX
members.description: Velocity along the direction of the X-axis.

members.name: MSGestureEvent.velocityY
members.description: Velocity along the direction of the Y-axis.

members.name: MSGestureEvent.initGestureEvent()
members.description: Initializes the value of an MSGestureEvent. If the event has already being dispatched, this method does nothing. This method is deprecated as of Microsoft Edge.
